defaultCulture
defaultThe PAC hearings, like the Poll
defaultard report a year earlier, revealed failings in the BBC’s corporate culture which were disturbing. In terms of repairing the journalistic reputation of the BBC after the Savile and McAlpine mishaps, the appointments of Lord Hall and James Harding offer som
defaulte encouragement. However, as Lord Hall himself remarked as the severances affair, there was a danger that the BBC had lost the plot in operational terms, and allowed an officer class to emerge, to the detriment of staff morale.
defaultThere was some telling momen
defaultts at the PAC hearings. At one point, former Director-General Mark Thompson, in trying to justify the excess severance payments to his deputy, Mark Byford, pointed to the amounts paid to his successor, George Entwistle, that were authorised by the Trust. A
defaultfter all, said Thompson, Entwistle’s entitlement when he resigned was to just six months’ pay, not the twelve months he received. In point of fact, Entwistle had no entitlement to any pay-off: he announced his resignation, based on significant failures of 
defaultleadership. Indeed, the Trust’s chairman praised his “honourable” decision. No cheque was needed.
defaultIndeed, the chairman, Lord Patten, remarked to the PAC that all BBC executives were over-paid, compared to the most important cultural executive in the UK, Ne
defaultil McGregor of the British Museum, who receives £180,000 a year. Immediately after the PAC hearings, former chairman Lord Grade appeared on Newsnight to state that the BBC had little sense of the value of money, because it received a guaranteed £3.6 billio
defaultn a year, thanks to the licence fee.
defaultLord Hall has announced his intention to cut back on executive numbers and benefits
default, as well as the committee structure that prevails in the BBC; and we must wish him well. An early test will be the salary he chooses to
default offer to replace the departing Director of Human Resources, Lucy Adams, whose current salary is £320,000 a year: or 1.8 McGregors.
